test-concept.consumer-insight-help-body:
SE:The objective of the insight is to make the consumer relate to a specific problem or situation that your new idea can solve or be helpful in.

Example:

"The ingredients matter when you cook food. Many people want to choose plant based for health and environmental reasons, but find it difficult to get high quality plant based ingredients that delivers on desired cooking performance. Imagine if there were great plant-based cooking alternatives without the performance trade off."

Top 4 advices when creating your insight:
  1. Use one insight for each concept. Hence, if you find that you actually have two insights in the description it is better to create an additional concept.
  2. Do not write the insight direct to the reader – keep it general. Hence do not write "You find it difficult" rather write "Some people find it difficult". Remember that people do not like when you tell them what they think.
  3. Everyone does not need to agree to the insight. If everyone would agree to your insight it is probably a too generic insight that does not give enough direction. Hence it should be possible for someone to say "No I do not relate or agree to this". "I would like food that is tasty, convenient, good for planet and health at no cost" is not an insight – who does not want that?
  4. Keep it short and easy to read, using consumer language - with as few words as possible.
test-concept.type-benefit: SE:Please write a sentence or two (2-25 words)
test-concept.benefit-help-body:
SE:Now it is time to introduce the benefits of the new solution you have. What are the advantages of your proposition that solves the problem stated in the consumer insight? You can write several benefits of your proposition and you will be able to measure the effect of each one of the benefits.

Example:

  • This plant based ingredient has a creamy texture that can stand boiling without breaking down
  • This plant based ingredient can be whipped into heavenly fluff in 30 second and frozen into a dessert
    • Top 6 advices when writing your benefits:
    1. You can choose between naming your product and brand in the benefit statements or keep it unbranded. Just ensure that you keep the same logic across all concepts you want to benchmark. Hence, you can write "Brand X now introduces a new line-up Y that gives the best cooking performance" or you write "Now introducing a product that delivers the best cooking performance".
    2. While in the insight creation you should avoid using "you" it is perfectly fine to use in the benefit as it is more "selling".
    3. State each benefit in separate sentences.
    4. Ensure that your benefits solves the problem set-up in the insight.
    5. You can enter more product specific descriptions such as tastes and packaging types and sizes.
    6. Keep it short and easy to read, using consumer language – with as few words as possible.
test-concept.type-reason-to-believe: SE:Please write a sentence or two (2-25 words)
test-concept.reason-to-believe-help-header: Ange "skälen att tro" för ditt koncept
test-concept.reason-to-believe-help-body:
SE:The RTBs are there to make it trustworthy that you can deliver the benefits that you have stated. There are many types of RTBs you can use, e.g. what kind of ingredients you use, your new productions technique, place of origin, endorsements that you might have, unique expertise or experience, test results or consumer quotes etc etc. Be creative in identifying what RTBs to use.

Example:

  • This concept was developed in a secrete Swizz lab by noble laureates whom worked day and night for 25 years to make this revolution happen.

    • Top 4 advices writing the RTBs:

    1. Be as specific as possible – the more specific you can be the more trustworthy you will be perceived, e.g. name people of places or specific ingredients when possible.
    2. You can use many RTBs as you throught the test will understand which ones are better.
    3. Be creative and pls remember that what you think is a good RTB could be very different from what the consumers might think is a good RTB.
    4. Keep it short and easy to read, while you at times need to use more complex statements in RTBs (names of ingredients or production techniques) try to use consumer language and as few words as possible.

report.Net promoter score (NPS) measures the li:
SE:Net promoter score (NPS) measures the likelihood of a respondent recommending a company, product or a service to a friend or colleague.
Respondents give a rating between 0 (not at all likely) and 10 (extremely likely) and, depending on their response, fall into one of 3 categories to establish an NPS score:
  • Promoters respond with a score of 9 or 10 and are typically loyal and enthusiastic customers.
  • Passives respond with a score of 7 or 8. They are satisfied with your service but not happy enough to be considered promoters.
  • Detractors respond with a score of 0 to 6. These are unhappy customers who are unlikely to buy from you again, and may even discourage others from buying from you.

landing.a taste of what's to come: SE:a taste of what's to come
landing.The food market is undergoing a vast tra: SE:The food market is undergoing a vast transformation. It has never been more important to involve consumers in order to understand the future food market and develop brands and innovations that really works.
landing.With InsightMe you can build interactive: SE:With InsightMe you can build interactive surveys with an easy-to-use application. Add questions, pictures, reactions and more to your test to create fun, engaging and accurate surveys. This is a faster, more agile and less resource driven way of gaining real consumer insights. InsightMe provide a solution that effectively bridges the gap between companies and consumers.
landing.It is the modern & easy way to to find o: SE:It is the modern & easy way to to find out what your target audience thinks
landing.The Insightme AI automatic advisor helps: SE:The Insightme AI automatic advisor helps and optimizes your concepts and ideas
landing.Run the test in your chosen target group: SE:Run the test in your chosen target group
landing.The Insightme consumer survey is designe: SE:The InsightMe consumer survey is designed to be both engaging & efficient for consumers and is based on a high-quality panel
landing.Get your results automatically presented: SE:Get your results automatically presented in an actionable way
landing.Get your key insights in a ready-to-expo: SE:Get your key insights in a ready-to-export format. Easy to tailormade your own reporting views as well as benchmarks versus previous tests
landing.More than just a test tool: SE:More than just a test tool
landing.Easy to use with quick consumer feedback: SE:Easy to use with quick consumer feedback
landing.Access to experienced design creatives f: SE:Access to experienced design creatives for e.g.  innovation and packaging tests as well as design of total brand concepts
landing.If need of support or further guidance t: SE:If need of support or further guidance the InsightMe. team of highly experienced research and  brand strategists are available on short notice
landing.Possibility to tailor your own research: SE:Possibility to tailor your own research set-up, upload your own segmentation model, choose among pre-defined questions or create your own, adjust your reporting views etc.
landing.High quality in both consumer panel and: SE:High quality in both consumer panel and questionnaire minimizing dropouts and engaging consumers in the right way
landing.Get help in writing, improving and optim: SE:Get help in writing, improving and optimizing your concepts with the AI automatic advisor
landing.Gather all your research over time in on: SE:Gather all your research over time in one place for easy access and easy to compare research and concepts tested over time (benchmark)
landing.InsightMe contains all key research mode: SE:InsightMe contains all key research models you need to build and track your brand, create and validate innovations and drive your business
landing.Possibility to tailor your own research: SE:Possibility to tailor your own research set-up, benchmarks, consumer segments, KPIs and reporting views etc
landing.Easy to share both concepts and ideas du: SE:Easy to share both concepts and ideas during creation as well as the results with your organisation
landing.If need of support or further guidance t: SE:If need of support or further guidance the Insightme team of highly experienced research and brand strategists are available on short notice, also for help with strategy and implementation in your organization
landing.Easy access to experienced design creati: SE:Easy access to experienced design creatives for e.g. innovation and packaging tests as well as design of total brand concepts
landing.InsightMe. contains all key research tes: SE:InsightMe. contains all key research tests you need to build and track your brand, create and validate innovations and drive your business​
landing.Test product innovations to understand b: SE:Test product innovations to understand business and brand potential of new innovations. Get deep understanding of how your product innovations score on key KPI:s, such as relevance and purchase intent, and if the innovations deliver on category drivers and desired brand position. Understand fit to consumer targets and see where the highest traction of your production innovations is
landing.Consumer segmentation, driver and barrie: SE:Consumer segmentation, driver and barrier analysis
landing.Create your own unique consumer segmenta: SE:Create your own unique consumer segmentation. Evaluate potential of different consumer segments and choose from who your future business should come from. Get in-depth understanding of your target group, e.g. their size and category spend, life values, category attitudes, shopper behavior and current barriers
landing.Pre- and post test of how well your mark: SE:Pre- and post test of how well your marketing communication performs against key metrics e.g.  attention, interest, desire and action (AIDA)
landing.Explore new geographical markets or comp: SE:Explore new geographical markets or completely new categories for your brand and business. Understand different market or category dynamics to prioritize where to grow
landing.Test draft or finalized packaging design: SE:Test draft or finalized packaging designs to understand business and brand potential of new designs. Get deep understanding of how your designs scores on key KPI:s, such as uniqueness, likeability and purchase intent, and if the design delivers on category drivers and desired brand position. Test relevance of different elements of your design to get actionable insights of improvements. Understand fit to consumer targets and see where the highest traction of your design is
landing.Get a clear map of existing positions an: SE:Get a clear map of existing positions and future potential positions. Understand positions both in terms of value as well as yours and competitors' strengths in positions. Identify market opportunities based on unfilled needs and gaps in the market
landing.If the brand is known by the consumer an: SE:If the brand is known by the consumer and can convert to purchase and brand preference? I.e. understand what the business and brand potential look like
landing.What the brand stands for and if the bra: SE:What the brand stands for and if the brand performs on the most important category drivers? I.e. does the brand stand for something unique or does competition stand for the same attributes?
landing.How well does the brand concept perform: SE:How well does the brand concept perform in the population and target group? I.e. is a re-position needed or can the brand grow with current position?
landing.What target group(s) the brand attracts?: SE:What target group(s) the brand attracts? I.e. does the brand attract "the right" target group profile or do we need to increase trial in other groups?
landing.Quickly understand a brands specific str: SE:Quickly understand a brands specific strengths, weaknesses and opportunities in the market. Understand e.g. brand sales effectiveness, short-term trend or long-term brand health based on consumer segment penetration and current associations
landing.Get qualitative consumer insights on e.g: SE:Get qualitative consumer insights on e.g. innovation opportunities, consumer usage, attitudes and brand perceptions, or co-create your marketing or innovation propositions with consumers. The consumer lab allows consumer interaction over a short or longer period of time with your specific target group
landing.Enables possibility to design and create: SE:Enables possibility to design and create your own tailormade test
landing.Understand what customers are willing to: SE:Understand what customers are willing to pay for your product/service.
landing.Create and test brand concepts (with tex: SE:Create and test brand concepts (with text description and moodboard) to understand business and brand potential of new ideas. Get deep understanding of how your concepts score on key KPI:s and if the concepts deliver on category drivers and desired brand position. Test relevance of different parts of your concept (e.g., consumer insight, benefits and RTB:s) and get consumer ratings on specific phrasings, claims and images for actionable insights of improvements. Understand fit to consumer targets and see where the highest traction of your concepts is
landing.Test draft or finalized communication id: SE:Test draft or finalized communication ideas (text description, images and videos) to understand business and brand potential. Get deep understanding of how your ideas score on key KPI:s, such as relevance and purchase intent, and if the ideas deliver on category drivers and desired brand position. Test relevance of different parts of your idea and get consumer ratings on specific phrasings, claims and images for actionable insights of improvements. Understand fit to consumer targets and see where the highest traction of your idea is
landing.Ongoing measurement of your brand-buildi: SE:Ongoing measurement of your brand-building efforts against key metrics, e.g. brand awareness, consideration, preference and key associations. Tailor-make your own reporting view enabling easy action
landing.Use InsightMes pre-defined segmentation: SE:Use InsightMes pre-defined segmentation model to make a data-driven decision on target group to determine who your future business should come from
landing.InsightMe saves both time and resources: SE:InsightMe saves both time and resources while not compromising in quality when it comes to consumer research
landing.InsightMe will enable us to find the rig: SE:InsightMe will enable us to find the right consumer insights to unlock the possibilities within juice and beverages. We need to be able to do more consumer research in an agile and fast way without comprising on quality to be competitive going forward.
landing.This was just a little sneak peek of Ins: SE:This was just a little sneak peek of InsightMe. We are happy to guide you through the tool and all of our products. Just let us know and we will book a meeting!
SE:Contact us today and we help you.
SE:This is InsightMe. We do what you want.
landing.Others just do what they can: SE:Others just do what they can
landing.Disrupting the traditional way of how co: SE:Disrupting the traditional way of how consumer and market research are done
landing.helping companies to more effectively fi: SE:helping companies to more effectively find the next generation food solutions.
landing.The team has decades of experiences when: SE:The team has decades of experiences when it comes to brand management and complex research projects with global and regional clients. In-depth experience from both start-ups and mature food companies to find break-through innovations and brand opportunities.
landing.We now took the opportunity to digitaliz: SE:We now took the opportunity to digitalize our process to make the companies’ innovations more scalable, agile and effective by building a SaaS business model.
landing.Experienced design agency that can help: SE:Experienced design agency that can help with design sketches for innovation and packaging tests as well as design of total brand concepts
landing.If you can’t wait and want to know more,: SE: If you can’t wait and want to know more, contact us right away!
landing.Our story text first: SE: The food market is undergoing a vast transformation. It has never been more important to involve consumers in order to understand the future food market and develop brands and innovations that really works. Not involving consumers have proven to result in more failed launches which is a waste of resources both for planet and companies. This we want to change!
landing.Our story text second: SE: With InsightMe you can select, tailormade or build interactive surveys with an easy-to-use application. Add questions, pictures, reactions and more to your test to create fun, engaging and accurate surveys. This is a faster, more agile and less resource driven way of gaining real consumer insights. InsightMe provides a solution that effectively bridges the gap between companies and consumers.
landing.We are insightme text first: SE: We have decades of experience of brand management and complex research projects, leveraging consumer insights and data for both start-ups and mature global companies to achieve brand driven growth and find break-through innovations.
landing.We are insightme text second: SE: In 2022 we decided to digitalize our process to make the companies’ brand journey more scalable, agile and effective by building InsightMe.
landing.InsightMe – the consumer voice in the tr: SE:InsightMe – the consumer voice in the transformation of the food system
landing.A digital research platform delivering r: SE:A digital research platform delivering rapid and actionable consumer insights for you to achieve brand driven growth and find the next generation of food
landing.InsightMe is the easy way to find out wh: SE:InsightMe is the easy way to find out what your target audience thinks
landing.Get your results presented in an actiona: SE:Get your results presented in an actionable way within days
landing.Choose from our pre-designed research te: SE:Choose from our pre-designed research tests with the possibility to tailor the tests to your needs. Add predefined or custom questions, InsightMe's segmentation model or your own. The InsightMe AI automatic advisor also helps you optimize your concepts and ideas
landing.Get your key insights in an interactive: SE:Get your key insights within days in an interactive dashboard and exportable format. Customize your reporting view by adding filters and benchmarks
landing.Easy to use with quick consumer feedback: SE:Easy to use with quick consumer feedback provided in days.
landing.Possibility to easily tailor the researc: SE:Possibility to easily tailor the research set up to your needs
landing.High quality data and advanced research: SE:High quality data and advanced research methodologies for meaningful consumer insights presented in an actionable way
landing.Choose among pre-designed research tests: SE:Choose among pre-designed research tests & get help in writing, improving and optimizing your concepts with the InsightMe AI automatic advisor.
landing.The experienced InsightMe team is always: SE:The experienced InsightMe team is always at your disposal
landing.Platform and questionnaire continuously: SE:Platform and questionnaire continuously being developed to be engaging & inspirational in our common ambition to create the next generation of food

BIC-popup-translations.The pre-defined questions and associatio: SE:The pre-defined questions and associations will be automatically translated into the language of the selected market for the test.  All concept texts, custom associations and custom questions must be translated into the correct language.

BT.Measure your brand performance over time: SE: Measure your brand performance over time
BT.How many interviews you should collect o: SE:How many interviews you should collect on a weekly basis depends on how often you want to analyze the data and on what level. E.g. if you want to analyze a certain demographic profile or segment.
BT.We recommend at least 100 respondents in: SE:We recommend at least 100 respondents in each breakdown/cell that you want to analyze.
